cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.MA 

This paper deals with decision-making in a game-theoretic setting with probabilistic payoffs and learning automata schemes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves decision-making under uncertainty, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves probabilistic models, which could fall under cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
